==Japanese==
{{janoun|はんかく|hankaku}}
# half-width
#* 半角[[文字]] (はんかくもじ, ''hankaku-moji'') In Japanese typography, half-width characters as opposed to full-width characters. These characters occupy a space twice as high as it is wide, whereas full-width characters occupy a perfectly square space. Usually in the form of [[romaji]], [[katakana]], and [[numeral]]s and used on [[receipt]]s, [[ticket]]s, and the like.
===Antonyms===
[[全角]] (ぜんかく, ''zenkaku'')